OL,3,CWho will be Guernsey's next Chief
OL,4,CMinister?
OL,6,FIf elected, he has promised to tackle
OL,7,Fgovernment inefficiencies and wants to
OL,8,Fsee a form of executive government
OL,9,Fbrought in, as seen in Jersey.
OL,11,FJonathan Le Tocq
OL,13,FIn the last Assembly, Deputy Le Tocq
OL,14,Fserved on Policy and Resources as the
OL,15,FMinister for External Relations - a
OL,16,Frole that gave him the ability to form
OL,17,Frelationships with the UK and the EU.
